      • getInteger

        public static int getInteger(java.lang.String str)
                      throws javax.script.ScriptException
        Converts a String into an Integer. If a conversion error occurs it generates a ScriptException which is easy to understand for the user.

        Remark: This method needs to be static because it is called from DispatchCommand, which needs to be static because it is called from the Dispatcher class without a specific object.

        Parameters:
        str - - String to convert
        Returns:
        The corresponding Integer value
        Throws:
        javax.script.ScriptException - when parsing the String was unsuccessful

      • GenerateValues

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> GenerateValues(double Start,
                                                            double Stop,
                                                            double Increment,
                                                            boolean Logarithmic,
                                                            java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> AppendToList,
                                                            int DecimalPlaces)
                                                     throws javax.script.ScriptException
        Fills an ArrayList with values starting for Start to Stop with either equidistant or logarithmically spaced values. If AppendToList==null a new list is created, otherwise the new values are appended to the specified list.

        This method is not static because it is used infrequently (as compared to getInteger etc.

        Parameters:
        Start - The start value of the new data series.
        Stop - The stop value of the new data series.
        Increment - When Logarithmic==false this value is the step size used to increment the equally spaced values; if logarithmic spacing is chosen, this value determines the number of values per decade. The sign of Increment is automatically adjusted to fit the start and stop values.
        Logarithmic - When set to false, linearly spaced values are generated, else the values are logarithmically spaced.
        AppendToList - When different from null the generated values are appended to this ArrayList.
        DecimalPlaces - If this number is different from 0, the generated values are rounded to the number of digits after the comma specified in DecimalPlaces.
        Returns:
        The ArrayList with the generated values.
        Throws:
        javax.script.ScriptException - When 1) Increment is 0, or 2) the sign of Start differs from the one of Stop when logarithmic spacing is chosen.

      • printStackTrace

        public static java.lang.String printStackTrace(java.lang.Throwable ex)
        Returns a String with the StackTrace. This method is similar to Throwable.printStackTrace but the output is a String rather than a PrintStream. If the passed Throwable has a cause, then the Stack Trace of the Cause is also listed.

        The returned String is formatted for use with a Logger, for instance m_Logger.

        This method is static so that it can also be accessed from IcontrolView where the default uncaught exception handler is defined.

        Parameters:
        ex - The Thwowable for which the Stack trace is desired.
        Returns:
        The Stack Trace of ex and of ex's cause if a cause is present.

      • Tokenizer

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> Tokenizer(java.lang.String CommandLine)
        Splits the given String (which represents a Script-Command) into it's Tokens. The Script-Command consists of either 1) a Framework-Command (e.g. MAKE, INCLUDE) followed by an Argument-List or 2) an Instrument-Name separated followed by a Device-Command and an Argument-List.
        A space character separates the Framework-Command from it's Argument-List, and also the Device-Command from it's Arguments-List. The entries in the Argument-List are separated by DELIMITER which is currently defines as a semicolon (;).

        Any leading and trailing white spaces are removed from the Tokens. Also, if part of the Command Line is enclosed within double-quotes ("), any DELIMITER found inside this region is disregarded. The double-quotes are not removed from the Tokens, therefore, the double-quotes appear in the Table when the Command Line is selected in the GUI. Enclosing part of the Command Line within double-quotes is important for Instrument Commands that expect a Command Line as input parameter as, for instance, the method Agilent4155.Measure.

        To use DELIMITER (;) or double-quotes (") in a script-command, use escape those characters (\; or \").

        Example:
        CommandLine = MAKE Tsample Lakeshore 340; GPIB9
        Tokens = "MAKE", "Tsample", "Lakeshore 340", "GPIB9"
        Command Line = PA Measure 0; V3, I3,V2 , I2; .tra\;ns; "Test ; Test"
        Tokens = "PA", "Measure", "0", "V3, I3,V2 , I2", ".tra;ns", "Test ; Test"
        This method is made static because it is accessed from the View, from Dispatcher and from Device

        Parameters:
        CommandLine - is split into Tokens
        Returns:
        ArrayList of String with the Tokens where leading and trailing white spaces have been removed, double-quotes are still present, escaped semicolons appear as semicolons.

      • getView

        public static GUI_Interface getView()
        This method serves as the Client Factory to return the View. When iC is run as usual (not as Unit test), this method returns the instance of the GUI_Interface returned from IcontrolApp. During Unit tests, the GUI_Interface of the IcontrolAppMockup is returned.
        Returns:
        The GUI_Interface of the IcontrolApp or of the IcontrolAppMockup.
